_header: Hail worth thou King of English erd
_description: ‘Ave rex gentis Anglorum’, a hymn to St. Edmund — six lines

BLAru231.Transcription:
Heil wrth þou king of englis erdekinges knyth of englen
                    eldeþu louerd eadmud martirs blomesose þe rose ant þe
                    lilie comesend þine bone to þe alweldindefor þe hele of
                    rich bileunde
BLAru231.Editions:
Herbert,  John Alexander. 
             Catalogue of Romances in the Department of MSS. in the British
                Museum.
         Vol. 3. London, 1910: 3.74.
